==English==
===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''post illa'' (verba); after these (words) through French ''postille''; a marginal note.
===Noun===
# A method of certifying foreign documents. Quaere: common misspelling? See note at [[apostil]].
#*Under the Hague Convention, signatory countries have agreed to recognize public documents issued by other signatory countries if those public documents are [[authenticate]]d by the attachment of an internationally recognized form of authentication known as an "'''apostille'''." The '''apostille''' ensures that public documents issued in one signatory country will be recognized as valid in another signatory country. http://www.dos.state.ny.us/CORP/msrfaq.html - 13k
